By: Hônen
Commentary: Here, of course, the whole matter hinges on intention.
---
By ‘profound faith’ we mean, not having the least doubt, but trusting
that the Buddha who vowed never to cast off the sinner, however bad he
might be, has guaranteed certain birth into the Pure Land to those who
do no more than call upon His sacred name but once.
